# Privacy, Retention, and Uninstall

- Classify and minimize personal data collection; collect only what is necessary.
- Document where personal data is stored (options, meta, custom tables, logs).
- Add data export/erase compatibility hooks when storing user-related personal data.
- Avoid logging sensitive values; redact tokens, emails, and private payloads.
- Provide uninstall cleanup routines with clear user-controlled data retention behavior.
- Never delete user content unexpectedly; require explicit opt-in for destructive cleanup.
- Use secure defaults for telemetry/integrations and require explicit consent where needed.
- Ensure third-party requests disclose purpose and avoid sending sensitive data by default.
